  "text": "Spatial integrity constraints have been classified in [CITATION_1] . In this taxonomy Cockcroft identifies also the (sub)class of topological integrity constraints, emphasizing their role as basic constraints for the integrity of geographical data. Topological integrity constraints are based on topological relations. These relations have been formally defined first in [CITATION_2] .",
